The JSE has adjusted the price bands across markets for trading on Friday in anticipation of increased volatility after the shock reshuffling of cabinet during the early hours of this morning.Read: Rand extends slump as Zuma fires finance minister Although the exchange rate of the rand has plummeted from R12.80/$ to nearly R13.60/$ after the announcement was made, the JSE opened virtually unchanged. The JSE Alsi is currently down 0.225. The JSE stated in a letter to clients that these adjustments were made based on historical event-driven volatility . The changes will only be applied on Friday and will be reviewed. The price band changes will also be applied across all derivative expiries. Current Equity Market Circuit Breakers: